6 airing this Sunday, November 11th 2018 on @pptvhd36 \u0e2d\u0e32\u0e17\u0e34\u0e15\u0e22\u0e4c\u0e19\u0e35\u0e49 #TheFaceMenThailand2 \u0e40\u0e25\u0e37\u0e48\u0e2d\u0e19\u0e40\u0e27\u0e25\u0e32\u0e21\u0e32\u0e44\u0e27\u0e02\u0e36\u0e49\u0e19\u0e40\u0e1b\u0e47\u0e19 16.15 \u0e19.|last=|first=|date=2018-11-07|work=@tae_kantana|language=}}</ref>\n:{{Color box|purple|border=darkgray}} The contestant was part of the winning team for the episode, but eliminated from the competition by master mentor.\n:{{color box|silver|border=darkgray}} The contestant was originally eliminated but returned to the competition by transferred into team master mentor, able to attend Master Class, but can't do Campaign.\n:{{color box|gainsboro|border=darkgray}} The contestant was originally eliminated but returned to the competition by transferred into team master mentor, able to attend Master Class and invited as guest in Campaign.\n:{{Color box|yellow|border=darkgray}} The contestant was originally eliminated but returned to the competition by transferred into team master mentor, able to attend Master Class, and returned to the competition in original team by master mentor\n:{{Color box|lightgreen|border=darkgray}} The contestant was a Runner-Up.\n:{{Color box|limegreen|border=darkgray}} The contestant won ''The Face Men''.\n\n* Episode 1 was the casting episode. The final eighteen were divided into individual teams of six as they were selected.\n* In episode 2, team Toni won the campaign. Moo nominated Pon while Sonia nominated Kim B. for the elimination. Toni didn't eliminate both of them.\n* In episode 5, Mentor Sonia can not to do campaign, But Ploy Chermarn take on the role Sonia Couling.\n* From episodes 3\u20139, Every eliminated contestant will be transferred into ''team master Lukkade''. They will be able to attend Master Class, but can't do Campaign.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://tv.line.me/v/4322011/list/266331|title=The Face Men Thailand Season 2 : Episode 3|last=|first=|date=2018-10-21|work=tv.line.me|language=}}</ref>\n* In episode 6, team Moo won the campaign. Sonia nominated Golf, Toni nominated Dom and Best while Moo nominated Paul for eilimination. Master Lukkade eliminated all of them.\n* In episode 8, William returned to the competition in original team by master mentor\n* In episode 9, Pitt Karchai replaced Toni who was occupied by his event, but after the campaign, Toni was back to the elimination process as Team Toni's mentor. After that, Kim G. won the campaign individually, automatically advancing into the finale. Sonia, Toni and Moo were allowed to choose any one contestant to advance into the finale from the remaining ten models. Sonia chose Luis, Toni chose Ryota, and Moo chose Poppy. Kat-chan, Andy, Film, Bom, Bank and William were eliminated.\n* In episode 10, Luis won the campaign individually, however there was no elimination so all contestants were put through to the final runway.\n\n===Campaigns===\n* Episode 1: First Impression, Runway and Self Administered 'Transformations' (Casting)\n* Episode 2: Equality by  Wonjin\n* Episode 3: Huawei Nova 3i Selfie Revolution\n* Episode 4: The Next Level of Clean with Comfort\n* Episode 5: The Destiny with Huawei Nova 3i\n* Episode 6: Extraordinary Journeys with Bangkok Airways\n* Episode 7: Preface of Final Walk\n* Episode 8: Chasing The Sense of Perfume You Can Wear\n* Episode 9: Accelerate Together with Toyota C\u2013HR Adidas\n* Episode 10: Final Walk\n\n==Notes==\n{{refbegin}}\n#{{note|1}} Dom was selected by master mentor and 3 mentors but master Lukkade selected him into ''team Toni.''\n#{{note|2}} Luis didn't get selected by 3 mentors but master Lukkade selected him into ''team Sonia.''\n#{{note|3}} Poppy was selected by master mentor, mentor Sonia and Moo, but master Lukkade selected him into ''team Moo.''\n{{refend}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{The Face (TV series)}}\n{{ThefaceMenThai}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Face Men Thailand season 2, The}}\n[[Category:The 