age=th-TH}}</ref> The season premiered on 7 October 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tv.line.me/thefacementhailand2|title=The Face Men Thailand Season 2 LINE TV|last=|first=|date=|website=tv.line.me|language=en}}</ref>\n\n== Auditions ==\n=== Myanmar Audition ===\nFirst casting began in [[Yangon]], Myanmar on 9 June 2018 under ''\u201cThe Face Men Thailand Season 2 Myanmar Audition\"'' with Piyarat Kaljareuk (Vice President of Kantana Group & Executive Producer The Face Thailand) and [[Sonia Couling]] as judges. The winner of the audition and runners-up will go to [[Bangkok]], [[Thailand]] to get a chance to audition again with [[Thai people|Thai]] and international male models.\n\n* Winner - Wai Zin \"Hernfah\"\n* 1st Runner Up - Zin Bo Chan\n* 2nd Runner Up - Myat Min San\n\n=== Thailand Audition ===\nCasting calls for Thai and any nationality will be held in [[Bangkok]], [[Thailand]] at Kantana Studio Ratchada on Saturday 11 August 2018. Aspiring contestants were required to be between 13 and no older than 29 years of age, and meet a minimum height requirement of {{convert|175|cm|ftin|frac=2|abbr=on}}.\n\n==Contestants==\n''(ages stated are at the start of shooting)''\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center; \"\n! Contestant\n! Age\n! Height\n! Hometown\n! Model coach\n! Master Mentor\n! Finish\n! Rank\n|-\n| Nirut \"Ruj\" Mitwatthana<br/>(Asharaf Alikan)\n| 28\n|{{height|m=1.83}}\n|\n| '''<span style=\"color:darkslateblue;\">Sonia</span>'''\n| '''Lukkade'''\n| Episode 3\n| 18\n|-\n| Yingphon \"Pon\" Charungphokhakon\n| 20\n|{{height|m=1.80}}\n|\n| '''<span style=\"color:violet;\">Moo</span>'''\n| '''Lukkade'''\n| Episode 4\n| 17\n|-\n| Jirat \"Golf\" Suphromin\n| 26\n| {{height|m=1.78}}\n| \n| '''<span style=\"color:darkslateblue;\">Sonia</span>'''\n| '''Lukkade'''\n|rowspan=4 |Episode 6\n|rowspan=4 |16\u201313\n|-\n| Dom Petchthamrongchai\n| 15\n| {{height|m=1.82}}\n| [[Melbourne]], [[Australia]]\n| | '''<span style=\"color:gray;\">Toni</span